HEADWORD: Residency
<hw>Res"i*den*cy</hw> <pr>(-d<it>e</it>n-s?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Residence.</def> <mark>[Obsoles.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A political agency at a native court in British
India, held by an officer styled the Resident; also, a Dutch commercial
colony or province in the East Indies.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Resident</ent>⟦br⟧
